In the lead-up to the Athens 2004 Olympics, Greek authorities dismantled the deadly groups November 17 and ELA, responsible for decades of violence.
A recent rocket strike on the US embassy in Athens has reignited fears of left-wing extremism.
Italian Foreign Minister condemned the attack, showing solidarity with the US.
Greek security forces are investigating the involvement of the extreme left-wing group Revolutionary Struggle.
Despite the attack causing no casualties, it raised concerns of a resurgence in extremist violence.
US officials praised Greek authorities' response and are working together to identify the perpetrators.
